    {
      "id": "JvJj2-o-wpnxUCjPikDba",
      "type": "text",
      "x": 3610.9743479223457,
      "y": 186.95891710469422,
      "width": 863.8894736205334,
      "height": 387.6240120213361,
      "angle": 0,
      "strokeColor": "#1e1e1e",
      "backgroundColor": "transparent",
      "fillStyle": "solid",
      "strokeWidth": 1,
      "strokeStyle": "solid",
      "roughness": 0,
      "opacity": 100,
      "groupIds": [],
      "frameId": null,
      "index": "b12",
      "roundness": null,
      "seed": 1182446015,
      "version": 404,
      "versionNonce": 2066323345,
      "isDeleted": false,
      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1782038345360,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "- The system should follow SOLID principles for\nmaintainability and extensibility.\n- The design should be modular, with each class having a single\nresponsibility.\n- It should be easy to add new vehicle types without major\ncode changes.\n- It should be easy to introduce new fee calculation\nstrategies (e.g., hourly, flat-rate, weekend pricing).\n- Components should be loosely coupled and reusable.\n- The system should be easy to test and debug due to clear\nseparation of concerns.",
      "fontSize": 28.190837237915353,
      "fontFamily": 5,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "top",
      "containerId": null,
      "originalText": "- The system should follow SOLID principles for maintainability and extensibility.\n- The design should be modular, with each class having a single responsibility.\n- It should be easy to add new vehicle types without major code changes.\n- It should be easy to introduce new fee calculation strategies (e.g., hourly, flat-rate, weekend pricing).\n- Components should be loosely coupled and reusable.\n- The system should be easy to test and debug due to clear separation of concerns.",
      "autoResize": false,
      "lineHeight": 1.25
    }
  ],
